cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentiment classification and utilizes dependency relationships among words. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a novel neural network architecture for the task. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses graph attention networks. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment classification is a common task in information retrieval.
